  "body": "### Issue\r\nIt was pointed out by @mbaxter in https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/2287#issuecomment-809641372 that it seems we don't have a strong reason to use slot number instead of epoch number to define the fork boundary.\r\n\r\nI'm üëç  on defining `ALTAIR_FORK_EPOCH` instead of `ALTAIR_FORK_SLOT`:\r\n- It's easier to derive slot number from epoch number.\r\n- Then it's no need to have config invariant `ALTAIR_FORK_SLOT % SLOTS_PER_EPOCH == 0`.\r\n",
